Card # 1

The Hierophant

It’s important to stick to the program this week and not change anything up – remain committed to the path you’re currently on.

The work you are doing is for a greater purpose. It may be something that lays the foundation for the future which allows for more opportunities and expansion.

You may receive guidance from someone you respect, this also may be a male figure in your life. They are looking out for your best interest, so listen to what they have to say.

Card # 2

Queen of Cups

Your intuition may be more powerful this week, so be sure to listen to your gut, dreams, and pay attention to synchronicities.

Others may come to you for guidance, and while you are the one to give it, be sure you aren’t also doing their own emotional labor. Boundaries are important as there is a possibility of burning yourself out, emotionally and psychically, and attracting someone who clings for the long-term who exudes toxic codependency.

Bestow your beautiful gifts of healing and caring for others, but don’t do so with a free hand.

You can expect deeper, and more enriching experiences of an emotional or spiritual nature this week, so approach things with an open heart.

Card # 3

5 of Wands

Chaos makes the muse. Take what’s thrown at you and transmute it into beautiful art. You are an alchemist and can transform anything as you see fit, if you do not succumb to the energies you are currently dealing with.

These may be internal conflicts, or external. Either way, you are torn, or a relationship to someone or something in your life is torn. It can be mended, but not through force.

If you find yourself stressing about money or expenses, then know this situation is just temporary and there are solutions available, it will just require you to work a little harder.

This card holds a lot of Saturn energy in reminding you of the lessons and cycles you have endured. You are experiencing a last little wave for the sake of your higher understanding, and new methods how you react and then act upon these situations are to be put into place.

Card # 1

King of Cups

Try your best to react to things from a more balanced perspective with both your mind and heart. Temper your emotions and use your intellect behind any decision making.

Don’t hold back in going after what you want but be sound about it. Flow into it. Align with it. Allow what you bring into your life to be stable, secure, and enriching, by approaching it that way.

You are supported and your vision can come to life, but it cannot be forced or coursed.

Card # 2

Temperance

Patience is important this week, as all good things come into fruition through time and continued, but steady, effort.

You might be bringing forth some results, or recognition for something you’ve worked really hard for, but also found a lot of passion and fulfillment in doing, making the rewards all the better, and more appreciated.

Either way, remain devoted and steady with what you’re doing.

You may also need to assess the energy you are exerting. Are you giving too much? Or are you giving too little? Balance is the key to a successful result.

Card # 3

Knight of Wands

A sudden burst of energy is about to materialize in your life, which is related to a recent investment, or perhaps a completely new opportunity with a small taste of what is to come if you take it on.

Be mindful of how you react to this energy, as it can yield positive results, success, and something you thoroughly enjoy. It can also create chaos if you are not patient and rush the process.

This may also be a time of taking a risk and bringing something entirely new into your life that could go either way – depending on your confidence in truly believing you are deserving of it. You could be incredibly successful if your approach is with an open mind and adventurous heart.

Travel may also be on the horizon. If you experience an increase in finances, consider traveling rather than buying things you truly don’t need. Invest into experiences.

Card # 1

4 of Cups

Think of ways you can bring excitement into your life while remaining on the same path.

If your romantic relationship feels dull, make the effort to spice things up. If you don’t feel blessed with what you have, recount and/or revise what you do and you will find the fulfillment you seek is right in front of your eyes. It’s important to switch your perspective from looking at what you lack to what you have. If you feel stagnant, get moving and shake some energy around.

Complacency will bring about more reasons to feel bored and displeased.

Don’t expect others to shake things up for you – take initiative, and those who follow suit will help enrich the connection you share together.

Card # 2

3 of Pentacles

This week is all about collaboration. Learn from others and share your ideas. Even if you have a different approach, you can still share things which can enrich one another’s projects, or even conjoin ideas and work together.

It is also important to keep pursuing your goals. You might be in a learning phase right now on how to integrate your tools and skills in obtaining something you want. You might be at the very beginning stages. As long as you continue to apply your best effort, you should receive what you’re working so hard for.

Card # 3

The World

This week is all about completing goals and creating milestones. You are going to receive the reassurance and recognition needed to know you have done well and the next phase is going to be more rewarding than you had imagined.

Be proud of yourself because you have done well. Take a moment to celebrate your accomplishments and count your blessings. This will align you to receiving more opportunities and invitations in propelling you towards the next level of experiences you have been wanting to encounter.

Consider more long-term goals you want to accomplish. What’s your next step? How can you take what you have learned and obtained into this new chapter?

Card 1

9 of Cups

Something amazing is about to appear in your life, and this is something you have been wanting and wishing for, for quite some time.

It is important to take into consideration that while you are getting what you want, it might not happen the way you would expect, but once it does, everything will make sense as to the method behind the madness.

Expect good news this week. But most importantly, do not forget to live in the moment, be present, and make space for joy, romance, and deeper connections.

Card 2

The Hierophant

It’s best to take the safe route this week and don’t do anything out of the blue. This isn’t a week of expanding beyond what you’ve know, but rather keeping up with traditions and strengthening your routine.

Showing respect for those with authority or more seniority than you will serve you in the long run, rather than making waves. You may also receive guidance or support on a project when you express your compliance and willingness to learn.

In love, you can expect things to get a bit more committal in an already established relationship, or perhaps deeper in the spiritual sense.

Card 3

Page of Rods

It’s time to take a step outside of your comfort zone and try something different for a change. Even if it’s fleeting, it could still be rewarding from the experiences it offers.

A new adventure awaits and it requires you to take a gamble or on challenges that you would have feared in the past. There is an eagerness to take things to the next step and to throw your best shot. Take on challenges with confidence and see them as adventures, and they will be much easier to accomplish.

Romantically, this is your sign to spice things up and liven your connection. If you are single, don’t be afraid to put yourself out there, however, don’t expect longevity from someone who rushes the connection, as it will dissipate just as quickly because of one of you getting bored of having commitment issues.

Card 1

5 of Pentacles

While things don’t seem to be where you want them to be, know that you have the power to shift them around. Sitting around and dwelling about the issue is not going to solve it. The more you allow it to bother you, the larger the issue will seem.

Try your best to recenter and take another look around. There are solutions, support, and resources available, you might just have to ask. As they say, a silent mouth does not get fed.

You will only feel alone, abandoned, like an outcast, or live in a poverty mindset if you give yourself permission to, by entertaining that feeling and allowing it to drag you down.

It would be wise to conserve your energy or redirect it towards other things that inspire you. Take your power back.

You may also be gifted another chance to rewrite a past wrong or to succeed at something you had once failed at. This time, you know how to go about it because you have learned from your mistakes, and this changed mindset will help you pick up where you left off and take things a step further towards success.

Card 2

XXI the World

You are completing a major goal or ending a cycle. This is big and could be a potential milestone, meaning that everything from here on out could change, for the better.

You’ve learned the lessons from the past, put your best foot forward, and pushed through, despite the trials and tribulations you had to face. Not to mention, the goodness you had encountered and memories you will take with you.

In love, this could mean a deeper commitment or taking things to the next level. In your career this could cater to a promotion or the recognition you have been working towards. Financially, this could be a goal you had reached – such as paying off debts or reaching to a level of stability that allows you to invest into something you’ve been wanting to for a very long time.

Card 3

Queen of Pentacles

You are supported, always, and all you need to do is ask when you need help. You can totally handle everything on your own, but sometimes it’s nice to feel supported and valued when others come to help you.

Work, home life, kids, and everything else – you are well balanced in tending to your own needs and handling your responsibilities and obligations towards others.

Things are about to get even better than they have been. As not only are you getting support, but you will also be raking in the rewards for the compassionate and unconditional love and support you have offered others.

Of course, you give without the thought of reciprocation, but others have been appreciative and want to show you. This goes for anything you have been pouring yourself selflessly into – the efforts will be matched. Consider this the validation needed that you are investing into the right things.

Ace of Swords

New energy is entering into your World, but with it, comes its own string of issues.

Just as you had thought you overcame the issues of the past, new ones circulate that require you to also be on your game and get to work on sorting out.

It is important to use logic over emotion, and while that might be difficult during Pisces season, you need to try your best to navigate through the thick of it. It can be easy to get carried away by your emotions or lost in your head. Grounding is vital to apply solutions that will work, and not just place a band aid over it or blow it out of proportion.

This week may also be a good time to cut out toxic ties and to set firm boundaries, so to not allow these old energies to be carried into your new cycle.

It’s time to expand further than you have been before. Dream bigger. Set the bar higher. You are aligned with limitless potential to create something wonderful.

If you have been waiting for answers, expect them to arrive and offer you the ability to navigate your path towards a clearer direction.

You will notice that much of your goals, plans, and even thoughts, are manifesting much quicker than anticipated, and so you best keep up! You are aligned with the flow because you are on the path towards something beneficial for your highest good.

Money, communication, and even romance should flow this week, allowing you to make secured plans for the future.

What is yours cannot be taken away – however – it can be delayed or riddled with conflict because of outside influences and where you are placing your focus.

Trauma changes everything. It cracks you open. It instills a need to develop a thicker shield. It steals from your quality of life. It steals your peace. But... once you start that healing journey & sit with, process, & heal that wound, it carves deeper depths within you that had once held so much pain, but can now hold so much love, appreciation, & joy for the goodness life also offers. You see the world differently. You experience magic that you were once blissfully blind to before those events shook your World apart.

Please know that there is always a way out of that darkness. Whatever had hurt you, will no longer have power over you once you take accountability in your healing.

You don't need to forget it ever happened. It's molded you. It will always be a part of you. But it doesn't need to have power over you. It can be your testimony that leads others out of that same darkness.

Card # 1

The Chariot

So much is changing as you have cleared your path from the obstacles laid out by old cycles and lessons. Now, it’s time to decide what you truly want.

You need to be serious about your pursuits and don’t allow distractions to get in your way, or temptations to steer you from this path.

You can do anything you put your mind to, but your mind needs to be focused, disciplined, and dedicated to the goals you are wanting to reach.

Don’t hold back from taking action when it comes to aligning with what you want. Make bold moves and know that you can achieve it all, as long as you believe you can. This may be a test of confidence, self-worth, and the willingness to go that extra mile.

Card # 2

Ace of Wands

New energy is flowing, bringing ease to old troubles and a rekindling of passion to already established projects.

Many of the new things entering your life are here to inspire you, and some are here to stay as long as there are spiritual undertones which give it purpose. Either way, this energy coming through is something that will boost areas in your life that need that extra push to get everything in motion.

You may be receiving a gift, invitation, or opportunity, perhaps even a financial increase of sorts. Whatever you are given, be sure to use it wisely and in areas that you want to elevate with it.

Card # 3

2 of Wands

What you seek is seeking you.

When it comes to love, starting a new business venture, or aligning with a creative opportunity – get your @$$ in gear and reach for the stars.

When it comes to your finances, anything extra you receive should be put away for the future as there will be future investments that will be worth pouncing on.

This is a time of stepping outside your comfort zone, being clear and direct about what you want, and reaching out to get it. Don’t go overboard with excess but don’t hold yourself back – a balanced and well-planned approach will ensure success.

You might be entering a new phase of experiences that are much different than you have had before. Growth is to be had, but you must take that leap first.

Card # 1

10 of Pentacles

This week is all about aligning with something that really feels like a strong sense of purpose. Something that is long-term and can carry you far into the future, yielding the same amazing results as when you first started.

The 10 of Pentacles is the card of legacy, in both beginning and sustaining a stable foundation where growth, joy, and the pleasures of life are guaranteed to be experienced throughout the duration of this journey – which is more than likely long-term.

This is a time of being fully committed to something that brings you a great deal of peace, comfort, and gets you excited when envisioning the future potential it could also bring.

Financially, things should be picking up as you are making way for more stability and a financial increase. You could be gifted something as a token of appreciation, which significantly helps you reach a goal, or you could be given a promotion or starting a new business venture that is incredibly promising from the time you start it, all the way to its completion.

Overall, the 10 of Pentacles urges you to build something that is lasting and encourages an abundant future.

Card # 2

King of Pentacles

Don’t just talk about it, be about it! Things are shifting for you in an incredibly positive direction. However, you still have a lot of work to do to ensure it continues to flow. The work is nothing like what you’ve been doing – as you’ve literally started this project, relationship, or business/career from nothing and have surmounted so much, gained wisdom, and are able to rake in even more growth, abundance, and stability upon what you already have.

The King of Pentacles as a person is a great advisor who will offer the guidance you truly need, support your cause, and even invest into your projects. However, they can be cold – somewhat emotionless when it comes to delivering such advice and are quick to call you out when you’re slipping. This is a King you want by your side, you just need to ensure you’ve got thick skin and to improve on the areas that have been called out.

When it comes to love, this is someone who will see you for you who truly are, and choose you based on your willingness to show up authentically. They will be supportive, loving, nurturing, protective, and love to provide. However, this is slow moving because they take their investments in love seriously.

Count on good things occurring this week in terms of the area of life this is resonating with – you will be receiving an energetic boost, financial gain, or deeper commitment in the areas that you want.

Card # 3

3 of Pentacles

It’s time to branch out and work with others. There may be connections surrounding you that are much different than what you are used to, or perhaps your team is quite diverse in what they bring to the table. As you come together, your diverse skills mold into the right working machine to function anything into existence that you are working on.

This card is all about collaboration and taking into account ideas that might differ from yours, but still add value to your projects. So reach out and see who wants to be a part of your team, or show up to your already established team ready to rake in the rewards from the successful projects you are working on together. As success, especially when it comes to collaborating with others, is ensured with this card.

You may want to spend a little time working on your budget and learning new skills to build upon what you have now, financially speaking. The financial advice you are given might not be what you want to hear, such as being more accountable and disciplined in spending/saving/investing money. Take into consideration the advice you are given and watch as things get tremendously better as you implement it.
A  client review from a reading last night 🥰. I love what I do!

Card # 2

The Empress

What are you creating? What are you currently working on? Be ready for the fruits of your labor to be realized.

You poured your heart and soul into this and your passion, while has been the fuel to your fire, has also been the magnet needed to align you with the highest outcome available.

You will be recognized and appreciated for the work you’re doing, be it in a relationship, at work, as a mother, or in your social connections – your heart will be seen and adored for what it has gracefully contributed.

In the material world you can count on your efforts to be realized as well. You may be receiving a boost within your career or business which brings you closer to your financial and/or professional goals.

Card # 3

Queen of Wands

This card can represent a woman in your life that is more than likely a fire sign: Aries, Leo, or Sagittarius. Or has heavy fire sign placements. This card can also represent you. However, it doesn’t have to directly be connected to the sign if the energy fits.

This is a very positive influence that inspires you to keep on track with what sets fire to your soul – to fan the flames of your passion. This could also be what you do for others. The energy is focused on seeing the light from within and expressing it, in making beautiful art as an expression of your soul.

This is a very sensual/sexual influence as well, and while the sacral and heart chakras may be activated within this energy, it can also be transmuted into creativity if there isn’t another healthy outlet for it (a worthy partner).

There is also a need to know your worth and to stand up for it. Don’t settle. Many may try to sell you short in trying to devalue you to fit their agenda because they refuse to put in the effort while trying to receive all the gains in what you offer.

Don’t let anyone clip your wings. Choose those who want to fly with you.
Happy Full Moon babes 😘

Cards # 1

The Fool & The Empress

New beginnings are on their way, presented as opportunities for the many things you have been wanting. Big changes are coming, and they may require you to take a leap of faith in order to activate them.

You might think something comes along that feels too good to be true. While it does encompass many of the qualities and experiences you desire, it seems almost unreal because of how abundant it is. Take this as a sign to move forward with caution, but to keep moving. Taking a leap of faith doesn’t mean rushing into something blindly, but rather deciding to venture down a different path that you haven’t experienced before, but have wanted to.

You have an opportunity to cultivate something that you have put into motion in the past, and this is something that aligns with your finances, career, and love life.

Cards # 2

3 of Inspiration & 5 of Inspiration

You may notice that there is a lot of activity and some clashing energy within your social circle, workplace, or personal relationships. It may seems that no matter what you do, there is just not a way to stand out or to be heard amongst others who are also focused on the same goal as you. This holds a lot of competitive energy, especially if others happen to be involved. If no one but one other person, or just yourself going after something you want, then consider this competitive energy as a sign to make different moves.

Basically, you are going after something that others may also be going after, or are trying to gain the attention of something that seems unimpressed because the methods used are overused.

If you are on the other side of this, where you have multiple options to chose from, then chose what stands out and not what’s just familiar.

Cards # 3

2 of Emotions & Knight of Inspiration

You know what they say about them retrogrades! It seems a reconciliation is coming into play, and this could be a past friend, lover, project. If you’re already emersed into something, then expect the sparks to fly as things get picked up a massive notch and push towards new levels of experiences and/or commitment.

This is coming in fast, with a passion, and a focus on mending what needs to be repaired. Compassion, forgiveness, and a willingness to understand from the opposing side of things is needed as well. Growth has occurred during this separation period, or if there was no separation, then there has been an “ah-hah” moment of clarity which triggered this sudden movement forward.

These deep emotions may be fleeting, and so it is important to understand that while the sparks will not remain there forever, they can still serve as that pivotal moment that ushered in new directions.

Cards # 1

5 of Pentacles | King of Cups | 7 of Cups

Let’s face it, you have options, perhaps ‘too’ many options and this is leaving you feeling unfocused and confused on what direction you should turn. There is no rush, so take your time, and most importantly, do NOT allow anyone to sway your decision through pressuring you, or acting like they know what is best for you.

You might not be seeing things for what they are and could risk choosing something that might not be the best for you, because you feel the other options lack what you desire, or you fear being left out in the cold if you don’t rush into a decision.

You are safe to take your time. Remember, these opportunities are presented as windows to new cycles, each holding their own lessons and experiences. The lessons and the rewards you will encounter all depend on the energetic match you are at when you make your choice.

You may need to collect more evidence before you choose anything, so sit back and observe. Collect your thoughts and decide from a place of emotional intelligence, and not emotional need. Don’t commit to anything unless you feel it in your bones that it’s the right direction to go.

Cards # 2

The Chariot | Queen of Cups | 10 of Cups

Be ready because events are about to speed up. Once you decide on where you want to go, there is no holding you back, and the resources, support, and energy needed will flow to you with ease. This is a time of connection, emotional fulfillment, and feeling supported as well as equally needed by others. Appreciation, admiration, and unconditional love are the theme for the week, or the goal you are wanting to reach.

With the New Moon, Mercury, the Sun, and Jupiter all being in Taurus as the highlight of this week, it is the perfect time to really focus on what you want to manifest this year. What goal, that brings real value into your life, do you wish to reach? You may find that you are already aligned with this insight and the path to get there is much smoother than you have experienced, making it feel like a breeze and enjoyable adventure.

Your emotional connections are highlighted this week, and you may set milestones or create lasting bonds.

If you are feeling troubled or facing obstacles along something that is bringing you down, then consider connecting with those you love so to lift your spirits, as that may be the energetic push needed to overcome what you are facing.

Cards # 3

8 of Cups | King of Wands | Ace of Swords

You may have recently parted ways with something that didn’t offer you the depth or fulfillment you desire. This wasn’t an easy decision, but it was backed with a nagging feeling every time you avoided addressing it.

The decisions you have made were with integrity, and you know deep down they were part of a higher path as well, in learning karmic lessons and applying that knowledge to experiences that were tests.

You are about to enter a new phase of experiences that may also bring about new lessons and cycles, but these are not as emotionally charged as where you have been and so it feels much easier to navigate through them.

Taking a more logical approach to any issues you may be dealing with could also be your answer. You may be getting intuitive nudges on what you need to observe, and with that comes the realization of the shift you must make within your environment.

These different paths seem to be aligned with your goals, but they are presented through different sources of experiences, and so it important you take the time to really consider where your priorities are, and which path will lead towards a future that offers even more expansive opportunities. This isn’t a time of settling, but for investing for something that will bring you towards even more.

It is important to choose from your heart and to take a balanced approach. This might be somewhat difficult because of the speed things and all of the energies involved. Also, keep in mind that while things have rushed in, you do not need to match that rush and can take your time in deciding on what to do.

Also, remain patient. Things are progressing and results/rewards will pile in. Don’t deviate from your chosen path and keep putting forth the same enthusiasm and effort.

Cards # 2

Ace of Wands, Wheel of Fortune, and 7 of Cups

Change is coming and it is going to be so much more than you thought it’d be. However, it might be easy to get stuck in a fantasy world and not truly see things for what they are, which could set you up for disappointment. Basically, while good things are happening, you need to be realistic in your expectations and not get carried away with yourself.

You might be at a crossroads where you have the potential for new ideals and opportunities to transpire from your choices. Remain grounded in the choices you make.

Cards # 3

10 of Pentacles, Queen of Wands, Justice

It’s time to be assertive in what you want and to approach it with passion. You may be inspired by someone this week, or perhaps an experience ruffles your feathers in all the right ways. You are entering a phase where you will be leveling up financially in which you will feel more secure and stable in your environment.

You might be signing a contract this week, or perhaps ending one that has run it’s cycle. Whichever it may be, this opens the door for new opportunities that bring you to this phase of leveling up. This can be a work contract, financial agreement, entering a more secure phase within a romantic connection, or something in that nature – it involves money, commitment, and aligning with a strong sense of purpose, passion, and feeling more comfortable within yourself and your surroundings.

If you happen to be the one delegating this contract, or have more push in the terms of how this situation is going to pan out, then make sure you consider what is fair for everyone involved if you wish to truly rake in the success if offers.

I know the world seems to be drawing in chaos again, especially here in the states with all this political stuff going on. Try to refrain from getting sucked into the illusion of separation/division & sprinkle your truth through acting upon it.

You may not realize just how capable others are of taking on their fair share, taking a huge weight off your back. Trusting others might not be easy for you, or it could be a matter of wanting to be in control.

These cards simply say, "Let go or be dragged." It’s time to start embodying the future you see because it’s not going to happen or will be delayed if you remain where you are now. It’s time to grow, and sometimes evolving involves eliminating.

Happy New Moon in Cancer & Nodal Shift in Aries/Libra! Oh boy... this week is the beginning of some MASSIVE shifts in our personal relationships & the relationship we have within ourselves.

The Nodal shift is all about Self & Others. With Aries in the North Node, we are more focused on what caters to our independence, authenticity, & the path we want to blaze for ourselves. The South Node in Libra is breaking free from people-pleasing & over-compromising to keep the peace.

I don’t really share my story often, but I have been felt called to. Here is a small part.

I'm not doing this for sympathy, I'm doing this in hopes it finds whoever needs it.

Being labeled as the “Canadian Elizabeth Smart” and the worst child abuse case in Alberta, Canada, my childhood was full of instability with a small periods of safety that was quickly overshadowed with a life of horror. This was done by my own family. I was sold for drugs and heavily mind controlled to remain within the environment. The mind control came with extreme degradation and beating down of the human spirit to program a truth and seek absolute control. It can be compared to being forced into a cult.

While my case made it far up the chain in the criminal legal system, it ran cold. The RMCP pushed my case hard until it got to the Crown where it was dropped. I was told “You’re in the United States now. They can’t hurt you anymore.” & the statute of limitations was the reason my case wasn’t valid. These things happened when I was a child. Money talks…

This cycle created a shell of a human, living life on the edge of fear with a highly developed martyr syndrome and horrible self-image.

I was never granted justice for what happened when I was a child, other than the justice I gave myself in forgiving and healing and doing my best in not allowing that part of my past to dictate my future.

I’m an empath & psychic medium whose gifts were heightened due to hyper-vigilance. You'll learn to read others real quick when you're in survival mode. Seeing your abuser’s pain is also next level shit...

Learning to hone your craft while healing from trauma isn't an easy journey. But it's fucking magical.

I specialize in shadow work because I have lived in the darkest corners of shame, despair, betrayal, and a broken heart. I worked through my own behavioral patterns that kept me in the past. I know the alchemy of turning pain into gold. When you have felt absolute lows and have nothing but yourself, you either evaporate into the darkness that created you, or you transcend and seek to discover the meaning of life.

I have had everything imaginable taken from me. But my spirit has always been mine
